Cell["\<\
When x=16, sin(\[Pi] x)=0. Estimate by using a straight edge, how much can x \
change and sin(\[Pi] x) still be within 1/2 of 0? (You can also figure this \
out algebraically and exactly using that sin(\[Pi]/6)=1/2.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.829737938718643*^9, 3.829737950878636*^9}, {
  3.829738030314198*^9, 3.829738209907251*^9}, {3.829738244219895*^9, 
  3.8297383649523153`*^9}, {3.829738480837295*^9, 3.8297385720848637`*^9}, {
  3.829741066739756*^9, 3.829741067010119*^9}, {3.82974166808145*^9, 
  3.8297416682276907`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"abf18838-e452-442a-b9b5-\
285e60485775"],

Cell["", "PageBreak",
 PageBreakBelow->True,ExpressionUUID->"4233dc66-3775-4f15-96e2-6ad589de8b5f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1(b)", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8297390093669977`*^9, 
  3.829739030122375*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2f2a7ea-f6c7-4626-b302-\
f7b742101b70"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We are going to compose this with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["x", "4"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "37bd3ed4-a115-4ec2-bf34-63fa30c0d844"],
 ". So we will be considering sin(\[Pi] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["x", "4"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "5b331395-1a0e-4165-973c-c8ddffda0a69"],
 ") near x=2.\n\nTo help you be more exact in what you are about to do, I \
have blown up g(x) near x=2. The function is very steep."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.829738619177335*^9, 3.829738711065216*^9}, {
  3.829739045669279*^9, 3.82973904834717*^9}, {3.829739166590626*^9, 
